%global packname  PPMR
%global packver   1.0
%global rlibdir   /usr/local/lib/R/library

Name:             R-CRAN-%{packname}
Version:          1.0
Release:          3%{?dist}
Summary:          Probabilistic Two Sample Mendelian Randomization

License:          GPL-3
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel >= 3.5.0
Requires:         R-core >= 3.5.0
BuildRequires:    R-CRAN-Rcpp >= 1.0.0
BuildRequires:    R-CRAN-RcppArmadillo 
Requires:         R-CRAN-Rcpp >= 1.0.0

%description
Efficient statistical inference of two-sample MR (Mendelian Randomization)
analysis. It can account for the correlated instruments and the horizontal
pleiotropy, and can provide the accurate estimates of both causal effect
and horizontal pleiotropy effect as well as the two corresponding
p-values. There are two main functions in the 'PPMR' package. One is
PMR_individual() for individual level data, the other is PMR_summary() for
summary data.

